                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d272">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/3978: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-07-24T10:00:00+09:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 24, 1921—10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 24—1:28 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>254. From Peking: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“July 23rd, 4 p.m. Expected storm against Peking is breaking. Following
                            upon series of recent defeats Kwangsi forces at hands Kwangtung, Hunan
                            is now moving troops against Wuchang. Szechuan and other wavering
                            provinces will probably join in attack <pb facs="0438" n="314"
                                xml:id="pg_314"/> on Peking unless Hunan is decisively defeated in
                            which event Wu Pei-fu<note n="2" xml:id="d272fn2">Vice Inspector General
                                of Chihli, Shantung, and Honan.</note> in Honan holds keys to
                            situation. Allegiance of all Yangtze Provinces very doubtful. Premier
                            tendered his resignation 21st; not yet accepted. Repeat to Department as
                            Legation’s 271.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
